{"id": 225025268, "title": "Burger battle, Greek fest and more: What&#8217;s happening in the Hampton Roads region", "text": "Our picks for what\u2019s happening in Hampton Roads: Greek Fest The Newport News Greek Festival starts tomorrow. Eat chicken dinner, loukaniko (sausage) pita and galaktoboureko, a custard-filled filo. Tour a church. Watch a dance performance. Shop the marketplace. 11 a.m. to 9 p.m. Thursday, Friday and Saturday; noon to 5 p.m. Sunday. Saints Constantine and Helen Greek Orthodox Church, 60 Traverse Road, Newport News. 757-596-6151. bit.ly/NNGreekFestival ___ Keep truckin\u2019 Williamsburg Food Truck Festival and Concert takes place this weekend. Some participating trucks include BigWife\u2019s Mac n\u2019 Cheese, Bald Guy Pizza and JiJi Frozen Custard. Admission includes a drink (nonalcohol or alcohol) ticket. The concert features The Deloreans. Proceeds benefit Housing Partnership Inc., a nonprofit. Noon to 5 p.m. Sunday. Williamsburg Community Building, 401 N. Boundary St. 757-221-0225. Tickets $15. bit.ly/WmsbgFTF ___ Lunch buffet The Lunch with Chef series kicks off with Stephen Kerschner, Chesapeake Conference Center\u2019s new executive chef. The buffet will include Texas barbecue brisket, chipotle lime chicken, potato salad, baked beans, summer squash medley, sweet potato and poblano hash, pesto pasta salad, assorted rolls and bread, Southern-style strawberry shortcake and iced tea. Donate a canned good or dry food item to get $2 off. 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m. June 7. 700 Conference Center Drive, Chesapeake. 757-382-2500. Buffet starts at $17. Reserve your spot. bit.ly/LunchChef ___ Burger battle CoVA (Coastal Virginia) Battle of the Burgers returns for a day of burgers and brews. Admission tickets include 10 burger-tasting cards and a subscription to Coastal Virginia Magazine. More than 20 restaurants will duke it out to claim the top prize. Must be 21 and older to attend. 1 to 5 p.m. June 8. Chesapeake City Park, 900 City Park Drive, Chesapeake. 757-422-8979. Tickets start at $45. covaburgerbattle.com ___ Afternoon tea Put afternoon tea at Zinnia on your summer rotation. Enjoy a pot of tea, sweet treats and savory bites with friends and family. Tour the museum to walk it off. 2 to 4 p.m. June 9; July 14; Aug. 11. Inside the Chrysler Museum of Art, 1 Memorial Place, Norfolk. 757-600-5538. Cost $35. Make reservations. zinniava.com/events ___ Other events to explore Zoo Grooves-A Jimmy Buffett Tribute: 5:30 to 9 p.m. Friday. Virginia Zoo, 3500 Granby St., Norfolk. 757-441-2374. Tickets start at $10.95. bit.ly/ZooGrooves Blackbeard Pirate Festival: 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. Saturday, noon to 6 p.m. Sunday. Mill Point Park, 100 Eaton St., Hampton. 757-727-6348. bit.ly/BBPFH Summer Kickoff Party: Noon to 10 p.m. Saturday. 1700 Brewing, 11838 Canon Blvd., Newport News. 757-782-5941. bit.ly/Summer1700 Coastal Virginia Bluegrass & Brew Festival \u2013 Chicken Wire Empire: 8 p.m. June 8. The American Theatre, 125 E Mellen St., Hampton. 757-722-2787. Tickets start at $35. bit.ly/CVABluegrass Low Country Boil Feast: 5:45 p.m. June 11. The Corner Pocket, 4805 Courthouse St., Williamsburg, 757-220-0808. Tickets $68. bit.ly/CornerBoil Rekaya Gibson, 757-295-8809, rekaya.gibson@virginiamedia.com, on X, @gibsonrekaya", "summary": "Good eats and drinks at area events, including CoVA Battle of the Burgers, Newport News Greek Festival and Zoo Grooves.", "url": "https://www.pilotonline.com/2024/05/29/burger-battle-greek-fest-and-more-whats-happening-in-the-hampton-roads-region/", "image": "https://www.pilotonline.com/wp-content/uploads/migration/2023/05/15/5OTKEF6VLVCTBFCUQLTLJXGLWE.jpg?w=1024", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:09:21", "author": "Rekaya Gibson", "authors": ["Rekaya Gibson"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.787}